Instructions on setting up Comicarr as a systemd service that will run on startup/via systemctl commands...

1 - copy the comicarr.service to /lib/systemd/system/comicarr.service
2 - edit the /lib/systemd/system/comicarr.service file (change user, group, python path, and comicarr location to user-specific requirements)
3 - create a symbolic link to it:  ln -s /lib/systemd/system/comicarr.service /etc/systemd/system/comicarr.service
4 - make systemd aware of new services:  sudo systemctl daemon-reload
5 - set comicarr to auto-start on startup: sudo systemctl enable comicarr
6 - start comicarr up:                     sudo systemctl start comicarr
7 - to check to see if running/status:   sudo systemctl status comicarr
